id: pm-nhby
title: "pm package init --capability <kind>: scaffold capability-targeted starter packages (commands|hook)"
description: "Extend the package scaffold (pm package init / pm extension init) with a --capability <kind> selector so authors get a runnable, fully-tested starter for the capability shape they actually want, not just the default 'commands' starter. kind=commands keeps current behavior (default). kind=hook scaffolds an after_command lifecycle reactor (the 'react to every mutation' pattern central to project management = context management): manifest declares the hooks capability, index.js registers api.hooks.afterCommand, and the package-mode sample test exercises activateExtensionForTest + assertRegisteredHook + runRegisteredHookForTest + deactivateExtensionForTest. Builds on pm-4ltc (runnable sample test) and exercises the runRegisteredHookForTest helper added under pm-miqm. Demonstrates the hooks-capability pillar end to end so authors can customize pm for any project archetype."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:cli","area:packages","area:sdk",pm-cli
